	version 7, missing

	syntax [anything] [if] [in] [, SCores * ]
	if `"`scores'"' != "" {
		confirm variable `e(dead)'
		global EREGd `e(dead)'
		confirm variable `e(depvar)'
		global EREGt `e(depvar)'
		confirm variable `e(t0)'
		global EREGt0 `e(t0)'
		global EREGa 0
		ml score `0'
		macro drop EREG*
		exit
	}

		/* Step 1:
			place command-unique options in local myopts
			Note that standard options are
			LR:
				Index XB Cooksd Hat 
				REsiduals RSTAndard RSTUdent
				STDF STDP STDR noOFFset
			SE:
				Index XB STDP noOFFset

	local myopts /*

		/* Step 2:
			call _propts, exit if done, 
			else collect what was returned.

	_pred_se "`myopts'" `0'
	if `s(done)' { exit }

	syntax [if] [in] [, `myopts' noOFFset]

			Concatenate switch options together
		*/

	if "`median'"~="" & "`mean'"~="" {
		di as err /*
		*/ "options median and mean may not be specified together"
		exit 198
	}
	if "`time'"~="" & "`lntime'"~="" {
		di as err /*
		*/ "options time and lntime may not be specified together"
		exit 198
	}
	local type /*
*/ "`xb'`index'`stdp'`time'`lntime'`hazard'`hr'`surv'`deviance'`csnell'`mgale'`csurv'`ccsnell'`cmgale'"
	local type2 "`type'`mean'`median'"
		/* Step 5:
			quickly process default case if you can 
			Do not forget -nooffset- option.
		*/

		/* Step 6:
			mark sample (this is not e(sample)).
		*/
	marksample touse

	if "`e(cmd2)'"=="streg" { 
		st_is 2 full
		local is_st yes
		local id `_dta[st_id]'
		local t  `_dta[st_t]'
		local t0 `_dta[st_t0]'
		local d  `_dta[st_d]'
		qui replace `touse'=0 if _st==0
	}
	else {
		local t `e(depvar)'
		local t0 `e(t0)'
		local d `e(dead)'
	}
	if _caller() < 7 {
		if "`type'"==""	{
			local type="time"
			local mean="mean"
			local median
			di as txt "(option time assumed; predicted time)"
		}
		if "`type'"=="lntime"	{
			local type="lntime"
			local mean="mean"
			local median
		}
	}
	else {
		local flag 0
		if "`type'"==""         { local flag 1 }
		if "`type2'"=="median"   { local flag 2 }
		else if "`type2'"=="mean"     { local flag 3 }
		else if "`type2'"=="time"     { local flag 4 }
		else if "`type2'"=="lntime"   { local flag 5 }
		if `flag'==1 | 	`flag'==2 | `flag'==4 {
			local type="time"
			local median="median"
			di as txt /*
			*/ "(option median time assumed; predicted median time)"
		}
		else if `flag'==5 {
			local type="lntime"
			local median="median"
			di as txt /*
		*/ "(option log median time assumed; predicted median log time)"
		}
		else if `flag'==3 {
			local type="time"
			local median
			local mean="mean"
			di as txt /*
			*/ "(option mean time assumed; predicted mean time)"
		}
        } 

	if "`e(prefix)'" == "svy" {
		if inlist("`type'", "csnell", "mgale", "deviance", ///
				    "ccsnell", "cmgale") {
			di as err "{p 0 4 2}option `type' not allowed after "
			di as err " svy estimation{p_end}"
			exit 322
		}
	}

	tempvar sigma
	qui _predict double `sigma' if `touse', xb eq(#2)
	qui replace `sigma'=exp(`sigma') if `touse'

	if "`type'"=="time" & "`median'"=="median" {

		}

		qui _predict double `xb' if `touse', xb `offset'
		gen `vtyp' `varn'=exp(`xb') if `touse'
		label var `varn' "Predicted median `e(depvar)'"
		exit
	}

	if "`type'"=="xb" | "`type'"=="index" | "`type'"=="stdp" {
		_predict `vtyp' `varn' if `touse', `type' `offset' eq(#1)
		exit
	}

		tempvar xb
		qui _predict double `xb' if `touse', xb `offset' eq(#1)
		gen `vtyp' `varn'=exp(`xb' + ((`sigma')^2)/2) if `touse'
		label var `varn' "Predicted mean `e(depvar)'"
		exit
	}

		qui _predict double `xb' if `touse', xb `offset' eq(#1)
		gen `vtyp' `varn'= `xb'   if `touse'

		gen `vtyp' `varn'= `elnt' if `touse'
		label var `varn' "Predicted median log `e(depvar)'"
		exit
	}
	
	if "`type'"=="hr" {
		di as err /*

		di as err /*

	if "`type'"=="hazard" {

		qui lnorma_p double `mg' if `touse', mgale `offset'
		gen `vtyp' `varn' = (`d'!=0) - `mg' if `touse'
		if "`id'"!="" { local part "partial " }

		*/ if `t0'>0 & `touse'
		gen `vtyp' `varn' = `ff' if `touse' 
		if "`id'"!="" { local part "partial " }
		label var `varn' "`part'Martingale-like resid."
		exit

			Comment if restricted to e(sample).

			created is shown.
			Do all intermediate calculations in double.
		*/

			handle switch options that can be used in-sample or 
			out-of-sample one at a time.
			Be careful in coding that number of missing values
			created is shown.
			Do all intermediate calculations in double.
		*/

	if "`is_st'"=="yes" {
		if "`type'"=="deviance" {

			qui lnorma_p double `cmg' if `touse', cmgale `offset' /*

			*/ -2*(`cmg' + (`d'!=0)*(ln((`d'!=0)-`cmg')))) /*
			*/ if `touse'
			label var `varn' "deviance residual"
			exit
		}

		if "`oos'"=="" {
			tempvar es
			qui gen byte `es' = e(sample)
		}
		else	local es "`touse'"

		if "`type'"=="csurv" {
			if "`_dta[st_id]'" == "" {
				lnorma_p `vtyp' `varn' if `touse' & `es', /*
				*/ surv `offset' 
				exit

			qui lnorma_p double `surv' if `es', surv `offset'
			sort `es' `_dta[st_id]' `t'

				*/ `surv'=`surv'*`surv'[_n-1] if _n>1 & `es'

			exit
		}

			if "`_dta[st_id]'" == "" {

				exit

			qui lnorma_p double `cs' if `es', cs `offset'
			sort `es' `_dta[st_id]' `t'

			gen `vtyp' `varn' = `cs' if `touse'

			exit
		}
		if "`type'"=="cmgale" {
			if "`_dta[st_id]'" == "" {

				*/ mgale `offset'

			Same comments as for step 8.
		*/
	* qui replace `touse'=0 if !e(sample)
